task: Load IC#1 (100% BOL NC) and allow the system to stabilize
Confirm plant is stable: a. Neutron power: 100% b. FW flow: ~78 kg/s c. SG pressure: ~2.7 MPa d. PZR Level: ~43% e. PZR pressure: 15.5 MPa
Ensure proper Plant Status a. Plant Mode = Turbine Leading b. Rod Control = Auto c. MSB = Temp Average c. MSB = Temp Average
Start Turbine Load Reduction to 15%: a. Set Turbine Load to 6.75MW at 1MW/min b. Press Go c. Monitor the Turbine Power decrease

Borate the RCS to compensate for the power defect and Xe concentration a. Set the selector to “Boration” b. Introduce a new boron concentration (20 ppm at a time) c. Repeat ‘step b’ as many times as necessary d. Set the selector to “Off”
Verify Step #1 variables once power demand reaches 6.75MW a. Neutron power: ~15% b. FW flow: ~15 kg/s c. SG pressure: ~3.6 MPa d. PZR Level: ~26% e. PZR pressure: 15.5 MPa
Start Turbine Load Reduction to 6% a. Set Turbine Load to 3 MW at 0.2 MW/min b. Press Go c. Monitor the Turbine Power decrease
Once Turbine Load reaches 3 MW: a. Trip the Turbine b. Verify Turbine Trip c. Verify Turbine Speed is lowering to 5 RPM
Set the Control Rods to Manual and lower all of the banks
Confirm plant is stable: a. Neutron power: 0% b. FW flow: ~2 kg/s c. SG pressure: ~4 MPa d. PZR Level: ~23% e. PZR pressure: 15.5 MPa
